# Auto-Scaling Policy and Resource Migration
## Assignment 3 — Cloud Computing | IIT Jodhpur

---

## 1. Scaling Policy Definition

### Trigger Condition
- **Metric Monitored:** CPU Utilization (%)
- **Threshold:** 70% CPU usage
- **Evaluation:** Every 5 seconds using `top` command

### Scale-Out Rules
| Rule | Value | Reason |
|------|-------|--------|
| CPU threshold | 70% | Industry standard for scale-out |
| Cooldown period | 300 seconds | Prevents instance flooding |
| Max instances | 3 | Controls cost and resource limits |
| Check frequency | 5 seconds | Fast detection of load spikes |

### Scale-Out Action
When CPU exceeds 70%:
1. Script verifies cooldown has expired
2. Checks current instance count < max (3)
3. Calls `gcloud compute instances create` with:
   - Machine: e2-micro (always-free tier)
   - Zone: asia-south2-a
   - OS: Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
   - Startup script: installs Flask + starts app

